    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "This FD-generation RX-7 is a prime example of 90s JDM engineering, featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The powerplant delivers a smooth, high-revving power band through a 5-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The front-midship engine placement ensures a perfect 50/50 weight distribution, complemented by an all-aluminum double-wishbone suspension for surgical handling. This vehicle has undergone a comprehensive vacuum line refresh and cooling system upgrade to maintain thermal efficiency. While it shows honest patina consistent with its age, the compression remains within healthy operational parameters, making it a mechanically sound platform for the purist driver.",
